  </div>

  <!-- EXEC SUMMARY -->
  <div id="exec" class="section active">
    <div class="section-title">Executive Summary</div>
    <div class="section-sub">Fathom Google Ads · April 15 – May 5, 2026 · 20-day analysis · Conversion: Qualified
      Sign-up</div>

    <div class="alert alert-success" style="font-size:14px; line-height:1.8; margin-bottom:24px">
      <strong>Account is on track.</strong> $15,369 invested across 12 campaigns returned 507 Qualified Sign-ups at a
      $30.32 blended CPA. PMax is running efficiently at $9.63 CPA and accounts for 85% of total conversions. Bot-free
      copy launched April 15 is already rated BEST/GOOD in PMax — 3 of the 4 new bot-free descriptions hold the lowest
      CPAs in the account. Search bot-free copies are in the learning window (20 days; Google requires 4–6 weeks) but
      early signals are positive.
    </div>

    <div class="cards" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); margin-bottom:28px">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="label">Total Spend</div>
        <div class="value">$15,369</div>
        <div class="sub">Apr 15 – May 5</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="label">Qualified Sign-ups</div>
        <div class="value">507</div>
        <div class="sub">All 12 campaigns</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="label">Blended CPA</div>
        <div class="value">$30.32</div>
        <div class="sub">Account average</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="label">PMax CPA</div>
        <div class="value">$9.63</div>
        <div class="sub">431 sign-ups · 85% of total</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid2" style="margin-bottom:24px">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>What's Working</h3>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong>PMax is the volume engine.</strong> Both PMax campaigns (US + CA/UK) are
            generating 431 sign-ups at a $9.63 avg CPA. Performance is stable. Bot-free copy added April 15 is already
            rated BEST/GOOD.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong>Bot-free in PMax.</strong> 3 of the 4 new bot-free descriptions hold the
            account's lowest CPAs ($8.61, $9.56, $10.09). Google is selecting them over older copy — a strong quality
            signal.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong>"Now With Bot-free, For Free" in search.</strong> Already generating 11
            conversions at $94.63 CPA — best CPA of any non-branded search headline with meaningful volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong>Bot_free dedicated campaign.</strong> 20 days old. 6.78% CTR and 2.81% CVR — the
            highest CVR in non-branded search. $140 CPA is a positive early signal.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong>Competitors campaign efficiency.</strong> $98 CPA and 4.96% CVR — highest CVR in
            all of search. 6 sign-ups from 121 clicks. Compact spend, strong results.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>What Needs Attention</h3>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong style="color:var(--red)">3 PMax headlines rated LOW.</strong> "Used by Millions
            &amp; Counting," "Sign Up &amp; Save Hours on Notes" (US PMax), and "Fathom AI Notetaker" (CA/UK PMax) are
            demoted by Google. Replacements are drafted in the Replace These tab.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong style="color:var(--red)">"Better Bot-free. Find Out Why." is not being
              served.</strong> In 10 campaigns for 20 days with only 51 total impressions. The algorithm is not
            selecting it. Replace at the 30-day mark.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong style="color:var(--yellow)">TCPA $180 campaign: zero activity.</strong> No
            impressions, no spend since April 15. Either no budget or a policy flag is blocking delivery. Needs a check
            before it goes unnoticed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong style="color:var(--yellow)">Non-branded US at $280 CPA.</strong> Volume is there
            (787 clicks) but 1.91% CVR is dragging the blended number. Copy refresh warranted at next review cycle.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-item">
          <div class="pi-text"><strong style="color:var(--muted)">Bot-free underused in Granola campaign.</strong> Only
            8.2% of Granola impressions use bot-free descriptions. Granola is local-recording only — Fathom's bot-free
            mode is a direct product win here. Should be pinned.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-title" style="margin-bottom:10px">Bot-Free Launch Status (Apr 15)</div>
    <div
      style="background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:10px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:24px">
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:20px">
        <div>
          <div
